To calculate how long it will take Tom to dry seven pairs of socks, we first need to convert his rate from per hour to per pair. 

Assuming Tom can dry a pair of socks in 10 hours, he can dry 7 pairs in (10 hours/pair) * 7 pairs = 70 hours.

Therefore, it will take Tom approximately 70 hours to dry seven pairs of socks under the given conditions.
